### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SOLEIL HOSTEL — REST Client API Test Suite
### Extension: humao.rest-client
###
### Select environment: Ctrl+Shift+P → "Rest Client: Switch Environment"
###   • local    → http://127.0.0.1:8000/api
###   • staging  → https://staging-api.soleil-hostel.com/api
###
### After login, copy the token from the response and paste it in the
### REST Client environment (settings.json → rest-client.environmentVariables)
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HEALTH
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Ping
GET {{baseUrl}}/../ping

### Health check (liveness)
GET {{baseUrl}}/../health/live

### Health check (readiness)
GET {{baseUrl}}/../health/ready



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUTH — Register / Login / Logout
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register new guest
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Guest",
  "email": "test@soleilhostel.dev",
  "password": "Password123!",
  "password_confirmation": "Password123!"
}

###

### Login (Bearer token)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@soleilhostel.dev",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

@authToken = {{login.response.body.$.data.token}}

###

### Login (HttpOnly cookie)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/auth/login/cookie
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@soleilhostel.dev",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

###

### Get current user
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOCATIONS (Public)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all locations
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/locations

###

### Show location by slug
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/locations/da-nang-beach-hostel

###

### Check availability for a location
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/locations/da-nang-beach-hostel/availability?check_in=2025-08-01&check_out=2025-08-05



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ROOMS (Public read / Admin write)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all rooms
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/rooms

###

### List rooms filtered by location
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/rooms?location_id=1

###

### Show single room
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/rooms/1

###

### Create room (Admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/rooms
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "location_id": 1,
  "name": "Deluxe Dorm 8-Bed",
  "type": "dorm",
  "capacity": 8,
  "price_per_night": 15.00,
  "description": "Spacious air-conditioned dormitory with private lockers."
}

###

### Update room (Admin only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/rooms/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price_per_night": 18.00
}

###

### Delete room (Admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/rooms/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BOOKINGS — Core business logic
# Requires: authenticated + email verified
# Overlap rule: [check_in, check_out) half-open, pending+confirmed block
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List my bookings
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Create booking
# @name createBooking
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "room_id": 1,
  "location_id": 1,
  "check_in": "2025-08-01",
  "check_out": "2025-08-05",
  "guests": 2,
  "notes": "Early check-in requested"
}

@bookingId = {{createBooking.response.body.$.data.id}}

###

### Show single booking
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/bookings/{{bookingId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Cancel booking (guest-initiated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/bookings/{{bookingId}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Confirm booking (Admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/bookings/{{bookingId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Update booking
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/bookings/{{bookingId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "check_out": "2025-08-06"
}

###

### Delete booking
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/bookings/{{bookingId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REVIEWS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List reviews for a location
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/locations/da-nang-beach-hostel/reviews

###

### Create review (requires completed booking)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/reviews
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "booking_id": 1,
  "rating": 5,
  "title": "Excellent stay!",
  "body": "Very clean, friendly staff, great location."
}

###

### Delete review (Admin)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/reviews/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CONTACT MESSAGES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Submit contact message (Public)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/contact
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Nguyen Van A",
  "email": "vana@example.com",
  "subject": "Booking inquiry",
  "message": "Do you have availability for a group of 10 in August?"
}

###

### List contact messages (Admin/Moderator)
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/admin/contact-messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Mark message as read
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/admin/contact-messages/1/read
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ADMIN — Bookings management
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Admin: all bookings
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/admin/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Admin: soft-deleted (trashed) bookings
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/admin/bookings/trashed
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Admin: restore soft-deleted booking
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/admin/bookings/1/restore
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Admin: bulk restore
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/admin/bookings/restore-bulk
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ids": [1, 2, 3]
}

###

### Admin: force delete (permanent)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/admin/bookings/1/force
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ADMIN — Customers
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all customers
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/admin/customers
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}



# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DOUBLE-BOOKING COLLISION TEST
# Send both requests rapidly to verify the PostgreSQL exclusion constraint
# and pessimistic locking prevent double-booking.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Collision attempt 1 — same room, same dates
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "room_id": 1,
  "location_id": 1,
  "check_in": "2025-09-01",
  "check_out": "2025-09-04"
}

###

### Collision attempt 2 — overlapping dates (should 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/{{version}}/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "room_id": 1,
  "location_id": 1,
  "check_in": "2025-09-03",
  "check_out": "2025-09-06"
}
